President Biden has announced key members of his economic team, including Lael Brainard as Director of the National Economic Council and Jared Bernstein as Chair of the Council of Economic Advisers. Brainard, currently serving as Vice-Chair of the Federal Reserve, brings extensive economic expertise to the role. Bernstein, a former social worker and long-time economic adviser to Biden, is known for his focus on worker empowerment and worker-centric economic policies. Other members of the team include Bharat Ramamurti as an Advisor for Strategic Economic Communications, Heather Boushey as Chief Economist to the Invest in America Cabinet, and Joelle Gamble as Deputy Director of the National Economic Council. President Biden expressed confidence in the team's ability to deliver on his economic vision and continue the work of building a strong, inclusive, and resilient economy.